2.e	To multiple two 16-bit numbers

•	Multiple two 16-bit numbers with the first number stored in memory locations 4600H and 4601H and the second number in memory locations 4602H and 4603H
•	Store the result in memory locations 4604H, 4605H and 4606H

ALGORITHM

1.	Load First 16-bit Number (X)
  a.	Load DPTR with address 4501H.
  b.	Read XH from external memory → store in 30H.
  c.	Increment DPTR.
  d.	Read XL → store in 31H.

2.	Load Second 16-bit Number (Y)
  a.	Load DPTR with address 4503H.
  b.	Read YH → store in 32H.
  c.	Increment DPTR.
  d.	Read YL → store in 33H.

3.	Initialize Result Registers
  a.	Clear R0, R1, R2, and R3 (set to 00H).(Result will be stored as R3:R2:R1:R0)

4.	Multiply Low Bytes (XL × YL)
  a.	Load XL into A and YL into B.
  b.	Perform MUL AB.
  c.	Store lower byte in R0.
  d.	Store higher byte in R1.

5.	Multiply XL × YH
  a.	Load XL into A and YH into B.
  b.	Perform MUL AB.
  c.	Add result to R1.
  d.	Add carry and high byte to R2.
  e.	Propagate carry to R3.

6.	Multiply XH × YL
  a.	Load XH into A and YL into B.
  b.	Perform MUL AB.
  c.	Add result to R1.
  d.	Add carry and high byte to R2.
  e.	Propagate carry to R3.

7.	Multiply High Bytes (XH × YH)
  a.	Load XH into A and YH into B.
  b.	Perform MUL AB.
  c.	Add result to R2.
  d.	Add carry to R3.

8.	Store 32-bit Result in External Memory
  a.	Load DPTR with address 5701H.
  b.	Store R3 (MSB) at 5701H.
  c.	Increment DPTR and store R2 at 5702H.
  d.	Increment DPTR and store R1 at 5703H.
  e.	Increment DPTR and store R0 (LSB) at 5704H.

9.	Stop Program Execution

10.	Execute SJMP HERE (infinite loop).

